M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 distinctly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 216-218
) 0.86-0.97 mm long, asymmetrical. Basal bulb moderately sclerotized, expanded apically to overlap basal part of apical process of median lobe. Latter trifid, with dorsal branches very narrow. Ventral branch of apical process asymmetrical, strongly inflexed and bent at apex in lateral view, narrowed toward mid-length and in apical half almost evenly wide in dorsal view. Parameres wide, lobed ventrally, each bearing small mesal lobe, overlapping apically. Internal sac complex, with dense denticular structures and few larger teeth in apical section.
